ZH: 太阳照射在我的脸上，感觉温暖而舒服。
EN: The sun shines on my face, making me feel warm and comfortable.

ZH: 医生用激光器照射我的病灶。
EN: The doctor used a laser to irradiate my lesion.

ZH: 这个灯具可以将光线均匀地照射到整个房间。
EN: This light fixture can evenly irradiate the entire room.

ZH: 照射在人体上的紫外线可以合成维生素D。
EN: Ultraviolet rays irradiated on the human body can synthesize vitamin D.

ZH: 汽车前灯的光芒照射在前方道路上。
EN: The headlights of the car shine on the road ahead.

ZH: 注意不要长时间被电脑屏幕的辐射照射。
EN: Be careful not to be irradiated by the radiation from the computer screen for a long time.

ZH: 士兵们用激光透视器将敌人藏身的地方照射亮。
EN: The soldiers used laser rangefinders to illuminate the hiding places of the enemy.

ZH: 阳光照射在湖面上，波光粼粼。
EN: Sunlight shines on the surface of the lake, sparkling.

ZH: 在春天，阳光照射的时间变长了。
EN: In spring, the time of sunlight exposure becomes longer.

ZH: 这束手电筒的光线可以照射好远。
EN: The beam of this flashlight can illuminate quite far.

ZH: 医生用X射线照射我的骨骼，以确定是否有骨折。
EN: The doctor used X-rays to irradiate my bones to determine if there was a fracture.

ZH: 这个照明灯可以照射到很高的地方。
EN: This spotlight can shine on a very high place.

ZH: 此刻夕阳正照射在大地上，景色美丽极了。
EN: At this moment, the setting sun is shining on the earth, and the scenery is extremely beautiful.

ZH: 这种光线主要用于照射文物，不会对其造成损害。
EN: This type of light is mainly used to irradiate cultural relics and will not cause any damage to them.

ZH: 这种照射方式可防止细菌滋生。
EN: This method of irradiation can prevent the growth of bacteria.

ZH: 在夜晚，月光照射下的花园显得幽静而神秘。
EN: At night, the garden illuminated by moonlight appears peaceful and mysterious.

ZH: 放射治疗使用高能射线照射肿瘤细胞。
EN: Radiation therapy uses high-energy radiation to irradiate tumor cells.

ZH: 多年的阳光照射下，这幅画的颜色已经变得苍白。
EN: After years of exposure to sunlight, the colors of this painting have become pale.

ZH: 请不要直接用激光器照射眼睛。
EN: Please do not directly irradiate your eyes with a laser.

ZH: 射手瞄准目标，准备照射。
EN: The sniper aimed at the target, ready to shoot.

ZH: 导弹发射后，被照射目标遭到摧毁。
EN: After the missile was launched, the irradiated target was destroyed.
